On a worker node, the following components are typically installed:

  • kubelet: The node agent that communicates with the Kubernetes API server and manages Pods and containers.

  • kubectl (optional): The command-line tool for interacting with the cluster (useful for debugging but not required).

  • Container runtime: Such as Docker, containerd, or CRI-O, to run containers.

  • kubeadm (optional): Used to join the worker node to the cluster.
